1
00:01:29,756 --> 00:01:32,459
Shancai, your motorbike broke down again.

2
00:01:37,130 --> 00:01:41,101
When exactly will you replace
that motorbike?

3
00:01:41,635 --> 00:01:45,606
Look what happens to you every morning.

4
00:01:46,006 --> 00:01:47,641
Your hands are so dirty because of it.

5
00:01:49,176 --> 00:01:50,477
Wipe them clean.

6
00:01:50,911 --> 00:01:52,346
Wipe them, go on.

7
00:01:54,014 --> 00:01:57,217
By the way, that tissue holder is Gucci.

8
00:01:57,284 --> 00:01:58,552
Remember to give it back to me.

9
00:01:59,453 --> 00:02:00,921
If not for you,

10
00:02:00,988 --> 00:02:04,191
our school has long entered
the Guinness Book of World Records.

11
00:02:04,992 --> 00:02:07,461
That's because all students here
have cars.

12
00:02:17,571 --> 00:02:20,440
STAFF PARKING AREA

13
00:02:25,012 --> 00:02:27,180
Shancai, you're here?

14
00:02:27,247 --> 00:02:28,181
Yes, I am.

15
00:02:28,248 --> 00:02:30,384
What's the matter?
Your motorbike broke down again?

16
00:02:30,450 --> 00:02:31,518
Yes.

17
00:02:32,586 --> 00:02:34,054
It's fine, though.

18
00:02:34,121 --> 00:02:37,891
-I'll just fix it later after my class.
-Okay.

19
00:02:38,458 --> 00:02:40,927
Sir, please take care of my lunch today.

20
00:02:40,994 --> 00:02:42,696
-Come eat it after class.
-Thank you.

21
00:02:42,763 --> 00:02:43,964
In this entire school,

22
00:02:44,031 --> 00:02:46,967
I think only you know
what an electric pot looks like.

23
00:03:39,352 --> 00:03:40,554
<i>Prada bag.</i>

24
00:03:40,620 --> 00:03:41,822
<i>So what?</i>

25
00:03:41,888 --> 00:03:42,956
<i>Look at mine.</i>

26
00:03:45,959 --> 00:03:46,927
<i>Burberry coat.</i>

27
00:03:46,993 --> 00:03:48,895
<i>As if! Look at mine.</i>

28
00:03:55,001 --> 00:03:56,903
<i>Limited edition diamond necklace.</i>

29
00:03:56,970 --> 00:03:58,171
<i>Then I...</i>

30
00:04:00,574 --> 00:04:01,742
So?

31
00:04:02,409 --> 00:04:03,643
You have nothing else?

32
00:04:04,211 --> 00:04:05,545
You lose.

33
00:04:08,315 --> 00:04:09,683
No.

34
00:04:10,050 --> 00:04:12,452
Come here. Get closer.

35
00:04:12,519 --> 00:04:13,787
Look carefully.

36
00:04:13,854 --> 00:04:14,688
What is it?

37
00:04:14,755 --> 00:04:18,125
Look carefully. Come closer.

38
00:04:18,191 --> 00:04:19,693
Look carefully.

39
00:04:23,630 --> 00:04:26,233
Julia Robert's nose.

40
00:04:27,734 --> 00:04:30,270
You didn't ask me
to have our noses fixed together.

41
00:04:31,838 --> 00:04:34,341
This is limited edition.

42
00:04:34,407 --> 00:04:36,376
I got it done in Beverly Hills.

43
00:04:36,443 --> 00:04:39,479
One for Julia Roberts and one for me.

44
00:04:39,546 --> 00:04:40,814
No wonder.

45
00:04:40,881 --> 00:04:41,815
No wonder what?

46
00:04:41,882 --> 00:04:43,917
I couldn't find you the whole summer.

47
00:04:44,785 --> 00:04:46,286
Where did you look for me?

48
00:04:46,853 --> 00:04:47,954
Paris.

49
00:04:48,155 --> 00:04:50,090
Are you insane?

50
00:05:02,302 --> 00:05:03,603
Hi, Li Zhen. Good morning.

51
00:05:03,670 --> 00:05:04,738
Hi, good morning.

52
00:05:07,941 --> 00:05:08,842
Hey.

53
00:05:08,909 --> 00:05:10,677
Are you reading the original text?

54
00:05:10,744 --> 00:05:13,313
Yes. Don't we need to submit
a report in Economics?

55
00:05:13,880 --> 00:05:16,316
Didn't the professor say
that we should just read this one?

56
00:05:16,383 --> 00:05:20,287
Well, I just feel that big-time professors
like Franklin must be strict.

57
00:05:20,353 --> 00:05:22,055
He'd surely not let us
off the hook that easily.

58
00:05:22,122 --> 00:05:24,191
So I wanted to refer to his original text

59
00:05:24,257 --> 00:05:26,326
and use it to study
his theories carefully.

60
00:05:27,861 --> 00:05:30,664
Then I'm doomed. I'll surely fail.

61
00:05:30,730 --> 00:05:33,166
No, maybe I just overthought things.

62
00:05:33,600 --> 00:05:35,502
Yes. You must have overthought things

63
00:05:35,569 --> 00:05:37,637
because the professor
only asked us to read this one.

64
00:05:39,139 --> 00:05:42,375
Actually, I think you're the only one
who really studies in this school.

65
00:05:42,442 --> 00:05:44,945
The others don't study at all.

66
00:05:45,011 --> 00:05:46,913
They just come here to socialize.

67
00:05:46,980 --> 00:05:50,784
They flaunt their cars, their bags,
and their new clothes.

68
00:05:50,851 --> 00:05:52,652
Qianhui is just too much.

69
00:05:52,719 --> 00:05:54,387
Did you see her new nose?

70
00:05:54,454 --> 00:05:56,056
It's worth NTD 500,000.

71
00:05:56,790 --> 00:05:58,458
A nose worth NTD 500,000?

72
00:05:59,192 --> 00:06:00,493
What's so good with that?

73
00:06:00,560 --> 00:06:02,128
People who got their nose done

74
00:06:02,195 --> 00:06:03,763
can't play the piggy nose game.

75
00:06:03,830 --> 00:06:04,865
Why?

76
00:06:04,931 --> 00:06:06,533
Because if they do this,

77
00:06:06,600 --> 00:06:07,934
it will protrude from this side.

78
00:06:08,001 --> 00:06:09,903
You're lying. Is that true?

79
00:06:09,970 --> 00:06:12,272
If you don't believe me, try that on her.

80
00:06:12,339 --> 00:06:13,640
You're kidding, right?

81
00:06:50,543 --> 00:06:53,346
It's just been a week since I saw him.
He looks so haggard.

82
00:06:53,413 --> 00:06:55,382
I heard he dropped out on his own.

83
00:06:55,448 --> 00:06:57,617
He just came to get his things today.

84
00:06:57,684 --> 00:07:00,787
If I were him, I don't ever want
to show my face in school again.

85
00:07:01,187 --> 00:07:03,189
I'll leave without getting my things.

86
00:07:03,256 --> 00:07:05,525
That's right. It's so embarrassing.

87
00:07:05,792 --> 00:07:09,095
He looks like a ghost.

88
00:07:09,863 --> 00:07:11,164
He's so pitiful.

89
00:07:11,231 --> 00:07:12,899
Then go and talk to him.

90
00:07:12,966 --> 00:07:15,769
I don't want to. What if the F4 finds out?

91
00:07:30,917 --> 00:07:32,118
No, Shancai.

92
00:07:32,185 --> 00:07:35,522
If you go and help him now,
who knows what the F4 will do to you.

93
00:07:39,726 --> 00:07:40,593
But...

94
00:07:40,660 --> 00:07:41,528
You have to know,

95
00:07:41,594 --> 00:07:43,797
Ah Shu offended the F4 last week.

96
00:07:43,863 --> 00:07:45,799
That's why he's forced to drop out now.

97
00:07:47,200 --> 00:07:48,568
<i>What's so great about the F4?</i>

98
00:07:48,635 --> 00:07:50,003
You think everyone's afraid of you?

99
00:07:50,070 --> 00:07:51,271
I'm not afraid of you.

100
00:07:56,276 --> 00:07:58,745
Do you know who you're talking to?

101
00:08:05,185 --> 00:08:06,553
He got the red card.

102
00:08:06,619 --> 00:08:07,954
That's right.

103
00:08:08,021 --> 00:08:09,422
He offended the F4.

104
00:08:09,489 --> 00:08:10,357
How can that happen?

105
00:08:10,423 --> 00:08:12,726
-It's his fault.
-Yes.

106
00:08:12,792 --> 00:08:15,395
-Let's go. Hurry.
-Let's go. Never mind.

107
00:08:25,238 --> 00:08:27,574
What are you doing?
Why are you gathering around here?

108
00:08:28,808 --> 00:08:30,744
Ah Shu is dropping out of school.

109
00:08:31,211 --> 00:08:32,679
-Dropping out?
-Yes.

110
00:08:32,746 --> 00:08:33,947
I'm his class adviser.

111
00:08:34,014 --> 00:08:35,648
Did he ask my permission
before he dropped out?

112
00:08:35,715 --> 00:08:36,549
Ah Shu.

113
00:08:37,050 --> 00:08:38,284
Professor.

114
00:08:38,351 --> 00:08:40,854
Ah Shu was forced to drop out
because of the F4.

115
00:08:43,523 --> 00:08:45,358
That's ridiculous.

116
00:08:45,425 --> 00:08:47,594
We can't allow troublemakers
in this school.

117
00:08:47,660 --> 00:08:48,495
Yes.

118
00:08:48,561 --> 00:08:49,462
Ah Shu.

119
00:08:53,767 --> 00:08:54,768
Ah Shu.

120
00:08:55,535 --> 00:08:57,070
Don't be a troublemaker.

121
00:08:58,304 --> 00:09:01,908
You have to be good
after you leave this school. Okay?

122
00:09:05,779 --> 00:09:06,746
Take care.

123
00:09:10,350 --> 00:09:11,785
It's time for class.

124
00:09:35,909 --> 00:09:37,143
Conscience.

125
00:09:37,811 --> 00:09:40,146
It's also what you call
moral righteousness.

126
00:09:40,647 --> 00:09:42,282
It's the foundation of being human.

127
00:09:44,350 --> 00:09:46,086
In Chinese history,

128
00:09:46,152 --> 00:09:48,621
the most famous righteous man
is Confucius.

129
00:09:49,022 --> 00:09:51,891
Let's talk about
Confucius' thoughts today.

130
00:09:53,259 --> 00:09:55,628
Confucius' central thought is benevolence.

131
00:09:56,262 --> 00:09:59,732
Benevolence is displayed by
behaving as you would like others

132
00:09:59,799 --> 00:10:01,367
to behave towards you.

133
00:10:01,935 --> 00:10:03,403
Don't do unto others...

134
00:10:06,940 --> 00:10:08,808
Shancai, what's the matter?

135
00:10:08,942 --> 00:10:10,276
I want to take a dump.

136
00:10:13,613 --> 00:10:14,481
You want to poop?

137
00:10:16,216 --> 00:10:17,817
Do you have tissue?

138
00:10:38,471 --> 00:10:40,507
What a crappy school and teacher!

139
00:10:40,573 --> 00:10:42,175
A student was already forced to drop out.

140
00:10:42,242 --> 00:10:44,511
He even said he's a troublemaker.

141
00:10:44,577 --> 00:10:47,514
And he's even teaching us
about conscience. It's all bullshit!

142
00:10:52,185 --> 00:10:58,558
Yingde University is full of childish,
materialistic, unsympathetic fools,

143
00:10:58,625 --> 00:11:00,493
especially those F4.

144
00:11:00,560 --> 00:11:01,861
They're big idiots!

145
00:11:01,928 --> 00:11:03,897
Pig Head 4!

146
00:11:05,565 --> 00:11:06,833
They bully people using their power.

147
00:11:06,900 --> 00:11:08,868
So what if your family owns the school.

148
00:11:08,935 --> 00:11:10,770
You better not mess with me.

149
00:11:10,837 --> 00:11:12,605
I'll never submit to you.

150
00:13:24,737 --> 00:13:27,073
If I really won't submit to them,

151
00:13:27,874 --> 00:13:30,076
why didn't I help Ah Shu earlier?

152
00:13:34,747 --> 00:13:36,449
I should go back to class.

153
00:13:51,197 --> 00:13:53,933
Shancai, are you going
to Statistics class later?

154
00:13:54,000 --> 00:13:56,502
I didn't enroll in any Statistics class
this semester.

155
00:13:56,569 --> 00:13:57,470
Why?

156
00:13:57,537 --> 00:13:59,505
Because I need to do part-time work.

157
00:13:59,572 --> 00:14:02,642
Then I'll be attending Statistics class
alone from now on.

158
00:14:38,311 --> 00:14:39,212
I...

159
00:14:47,887 --> 00:14:48,855
I'm sorry.

160
00:14:49,822 --> 00:14:51,891
I'm sorry. I didn't notice you.

161
00:14:52,291 --> 00:14:53,860
You bumped into me.

162
00:14:53,926 --> 00:14:57,430
If you had bumped into other students,
would you still apologize, Professor?

163
00:14:57,497 --> 00:14:58,398
I will.

164
00:14:58,464 --> 00:15:00,133
I'll wipe it for you. Here.

165
00:15:00,199 --> 00:15:01,434
Professor.

166
00:15:01,501 --> 00:15:03,202
You stepped on my foot.

167
00:15:03,870 --> 00:15:05,471
I'm sorry. I'll wipe it for you.

168
00:15:06,973 --> 00:15:09,942
If apologizing is enough,
what do we need the police for?

169
00:15:14,714 --> 00:15:15,681
I know.

170
00:15:16,549 --> 00:15:18,384
I'm a troublemaker in this school.

171
00:15:18,918 --> 00:15:21,387
You won't see me again from now on.

172
00:15:21,454 --> 00:15:22,555
Whatever. Get far away from me.

173
00:15:22,622 --> 00:15:24,624
Don't hit me.

174
00:15:42,175 --> 00:15:44,744
Young Master Daoming Si
is not in a good mood today.

175
00:15:44,811 --> 00:15:47,814
How can you make a mess
in the school's beautiful corridor?

176
00:15:47,880 --> 00:15:49,115
You shouldn't do that.

177
00:15:50,850 --> 00:15:55,021
<i>I can't believe such an arrogant breed
of people exist in this world.</i>

178
00:16:14,140 --> 00:16:16,375
Lei, what are you doing? Let's go.

179
00:16:30,957 --> 00:16:33,226
<i>Is F4 really that awful?</i>

180
00:16:33,860 --> 00:16:35,228
Yes, I'm telling you.

181
00:16:35,294 --> 00:16:36,762
Especially their leader,

182
00:16:36,829 --> 00:16:39,565
that Daoming Si, he's so despicable.

183
00:16:39,966 --> 00:16:42,768
I really want to let you see
their evil and hateful looks.

184
00:16:43,236 --> 00:16:45,605
I really want to see the F4.

185
00:16:45,671 --> 00:16:47,874
Xiaoyou, what kind
of facial expression is that?

186
00:16:47,940 --> 00:16:48,808
No.

187
00:16:48,875 --> 00:16:51,577
Boys in other universities
are all so lame.

188
00:16:51,644 --> 00:16:53,346
Please, what's wrong with that?

189
00:16:53,412 --> 00:16:54,480
Let me tell you,

190
00:16:54,547 --> 00:16:56,816
our school is no different from hell.

191
00:16:56,883 --> 00:16:59,585
Because that school is owned
by their families,

192
00:16:59,652 --> 00:17:02,288
it seems they want to train them to become
the successors of their families.

193
00:17:02,355 --> 00:17:05,258
That's why they can do
whatever they want in school.

194
00:17:05,324 --> 00:17:07,059
Nobody dares to say anything.

195
00:17:07,126 --> 00:17:09,529
I get mad just thinking about it.
I'm not talking about them anymore.

196
00:17:09,595 --> 00:17:11,797
Tell me about them. I'm interested.

197
00:17:11,864 --> 00:17:12,798
I don't want to.

198
00:17:12,865 --> 00:17:13,699
Tell me.

199
00:17:13,766 --> 00:17:15,535
-No.
-Tell me.

200
00:17:15,902 --> 00:17:17,036
No.

201
00:17:17,370 --> 00:17:20,473
At least tell me why they're called F4.

202
00:17:22,608 --> 00:17:24,844
The reason is hilarious.

203
00:17:24,911 --> 00:17:27,380
F4 means Flower Four.

204
00:17:27,446 --> 00:17:28,714
It's embarrassing, right?

205
00:17:30,082 --> 00:17:32,785
That means they're
as beautiful as flowers.

206
00:17:32,852 --> 00:17:35,187
And super rich.

207
00:17:35,254 --> 00:17:36,589
You're so boy crazy.

208
00:17:36,656 --> 00:17:40,459
I'm telling you,
the four of them may look good,

209
00:17:40,526 --> 00:17:42,628
but they're all morons.

210
00:17:42,695 --> 00:17:44,230
And they like bullying people.

211
00:17:44,297 --> 00:17:45,598
They don't have any compassion.

212
00:17:45,665 --> 00:17:47,133
I call them Pig Head 4.

213
00:17:47,199 --> 00:17:50,002
Are they all as bad as you say they are?

214
00:17:55,708 --> 00:18:00,046
Maybe one of them is different.

215
00:18:00,880 --> 00:18:03,416
It seems he's more decent than the others.

216
00:18:06,586 --> 00:18:10,690
Shancai, are you interested
in the one that seems different?

217
00:18:10,756 --> 00:18:12,325
I'm not.

218
00:18:12,692 --> 00:18:13,793
I've long made my decision.

219
00:18:13,859 --> 00:18:16,796
I'll stay away from trouble
for four years.

220
00:18:16,862 --> 00:18:19,398
I won't interfere with anything
unrelated to me.

221
00:18:19,465 --> 00:18:22,768
I don't belong in that school anyway.

222
00:18:23,302 --> 00:18:24,704
If not for my mom,

223
00:18:25,037 --> 00:18:26,906
I won't study in that school.

224
00:18:30,409 --> 00:18:31,377
Shancai...

225
00:18:32,078 --> 00:18:34,714
You've changed a lot
after you studied in Yingde.

226
00:18:35,581 --> 00:18:37,483
I remember when we first met
each other in senior high,

227
00:18:37,550 --> 00:18:40,186
a very fat guy in class was bullying me.

228
00:18:40,620 --> 00:18:41,921
I already forgot his name.

229
00:18:41,988 --> 00:18:45,024
You stood up for me
and forced him to apologize to me.

230
00:18:45,925 --> 00:18:48,060
In the three years after that,

231
00:18:48,127 --> 00:18:52,331
you were so nice to all of us,
to all our classmates.

232
00:18:54,567 --> 00:18:57,203
I don't know why you've changed a lot now.

233
00:18:58,004 --> 00:19:00,006
You're not the Shancai I know anymore.

234
00:19:06,112 --> 00:19:09,715
<i>Actually, I also hate myself right now.</i>

235
00:19:09,782 --> 00:19:12,785
<i>I'm such a coward.</i>

236
00:19:12,852 --> 00:19:16,022
<i>I put on a mask every day
and pretend to smile.</i>

237
00:19:16,822 --> 00:19:19,358
<i>I couldn't even help Ah Shu.</i>

238
00:19:19,959 --> 00:19:22,795
<i>I'm just going with the flow
and waiting for time to pass by.</i>

239
00:19:23,863 --> 00:19:25,898
<i>I shouldn't be this kind of person.</i>

240
00:19:52,458 --> 00:19:53,526
I'm home.

241
00:19:55,094 --> 00:19:56,762
Shancai, you're home.

242
00:19:56,829 --> 00:19:58,097
Look at me.

243
00:19:58,564 --> 00:20:00,166
Mom, you dyed your hair?

244
00:20:00,232 --> 00:20:01,434
You noticed?

245
00:20:01,500 --> 00:20:02,668
I did it myself.

246
00:20:02,735 --> 00:20:05,037
I only spent NTD 260. I dyed it myself.

247
00:20:05,438 --> 00:20:06,939
You look like a foreigner.

248
00:20:07,006 --> 00:20:07,840
That's great.

249
00:20:07,907 --> 00:20:10,242
It's also good if you can get
a foreigner boyfriend.

250
00:20:10,342 --> 00:20:13,379
Did you meet any nice man in school today?

251
00:20:13,446 --> 00:20:15,247
Mom, I go to school to study.

252
00:20:15,314 --> 00:20:16,515
What does it have to do with men?

253
00:20:16,582 --> 00:20:19,285
Study, yes. You have to study too.

254
00:20:19,351 --> 00:20:21,220
However, your books are so expensive.

255
00:20:21,287 --> 00:20:24,623
You have to meet nice men
so that it'll be worth it.

256
00:20:25,691 --> 00:20:26,792
Mom, that's how you are.

257
00:20:26,859 --> 00:20:28,027
You love to keep up appearances.

258
00:20:28,094 --> 00:20:29,228
We don't have much money.

259
00:20:29,295 --> 00:20:30,596
You have to live in such a big house.

260
00:20:30,663 --> 00:20:32,331
You let me study
in such an expensive school.

261
00:20:33,232 --> 00:20:34,100
Dad.

262
00:20:34,166 --> 00:20:36,268
